jobs.prompt:
You are working in Code&DBs/Workflow/runtime/manifest_generator.py.

The ManifestGenerator currently produces V1 manifests (with layout.children). Update it to produce V2 manifests (version:2, grid:'4x4', quadrants:{...}).

The registered module IDs are:
Display: metric, stat-row, chart, activity-feed, status-grid, markdown, key-value, data-table
Input: text-input, intent-box, dropdown-select, button-row, file-drop
Tool: dispatch-form, search-panel, document-processor, data-pipeline
Composite: workflow-status, bug-card, model-card, registry-browser

Update the LLM prompt in _build_generate_prompt() to:
1. Tell the LLM to output a V2 manifest JSON: {version: 2, grid: '4x4', quadrants: {A1: {module, span?, config?}, ...}}
2. Include the full list of registered module IDs with their config options
3. Include example configs for common modules:
   - data-table: {objectType: 'contact', publishSelection: 'contact', columns: [...]}
   - metric: {label: '...', value: '...', color: '#...'}
   - chart: {endpoint: '...', path: '...', type: 'bar', xKey: '...', yKey: '...'}
   - search-panel: {objectType: '...', placeholder: '...'}
   - button-row: {actions: [{label, variant, createObject?: {typeId, defaults}}]}
   - activity-feed: {title: '...'}
   - key-value: {subscribeSelection: '...', title: '...'}
4. Tell the LLM it can also output an optional 'object_types' array alongside the manifest to create new data types
5. Parse the LLM response extracting the V2 manifest JSON
6. Validate: version must be 2, quadrants must only reference registered module IDs

Also update the generate() method to:
- If the LLM output includes object_types, create them in Postgres before saving the manifest
- Save the manifest as status='active' not 'draft'

Write the updated file. Use the existing claude CLI call pattern (subprocess with --model claude-sonnet-4-6).
